content.text:
Found a clear bug in the D2 consecutive_retries handler. The `AIM_STILL` case is missing the `attack_type` check.

**C code** (main_d2/ai.cpp:998-1003):
```c
case AIM_STILL:
    if (robptr->attack_type)
        move_towards_segment_center(obj);
    else if (!((aip->behavior == AIB_STILL) || (aip->behavior == AIB_STATION) || (aip->behavior == AIB_FOLLOW)))
        attempt_to_resume_path(obj);
    break;
```

**OCaml code** (ox_ai_frame.ml:1842-1844) — missing the `attack_type` branch:
```ocaml
| m when m = aim_still ->
    if not (!behavior = aib_still || !behavior = aib_station || !behavior = aib_follow)
    then unpack_path_state (Effect.perform Attempt_to_resume_path)
```

When `attack_type` is nonzero, C calls `move_towards_segment_center` instead of checking behavior. OCaml skips this entirely. Let me fix it.

